Representative TEM image shows that the typical product contains a variety of C-dots well dispersed across the whole section, with the average diameter of 10nm (Fig. 2
                        ). The surface functional groups of C-dots are further characterized by FTIR spectra (Fig. 3
                        ), in which the characteristic absorption bands are emerged at 3300cm−1 for OH and NH stretching vibrations, 2940cm−1 for CH stretching vibrations, 1660cm−1 for CO stretching vibrations, and 1560cm−1 for NH2 stretching vibrations. Besides, the bands in the range of 1050–1360cm−1 are assigned to the large amount of CO groups [24]. All of the above results demonstrate the existence of hydroxyl and carboxylic groups on the surface of C-dots.
